OL,3,CTwo men guilty in Blenheim Palace gold
OL,4,Ctoilet theft case
OL,6,F"While none of the gold was ever
OL,7,Frecovered ` no doubt having been
OL,8,Fbroken up or melted down and sold on
OL,9,Fsoon after it was stolen ` we are
OL,10,Fconfident this prosecution has played
OL,11,Fa part in disrupting a wider crime and
OL,12,Fmoney laundering network."
OL,14,FHeather Carter, Managing Director at
OL,15,FBlenheim Palace said she is "thrilled"
OL,16,Fwith the outcome of the trial.
OL,18,F"Five years after the theft of
OL,19,F'America' to have the individuals
OL,20,Finvolved brought to justice is great
OL,21,Fnews," said Carter.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/10
